    <h1>Badang And&#xD;&#xA;The Sin&#xAD;ga&#xAD;pore Stone</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200814/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-14"><time>2020-08-14</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The third ses­sion of a sto­ry­telling series fea­tur­ing lo­cal folk tales by Gate­way Theatre tells of Badang, a poor fish­er­man who dreams about be­com­ing strong. One day, he finds a wa­ter mon­ster eat­ing his fish and threat­ens to kill him. The mon­ster of­fers Badang any power in ex­change for his free­dom, but it comes at a price. Gate­way Theatre sup­ports made-in-Sin­ga­pore works and pro­motes pos­i­tive mes­sages and so­cial values to chil­dren, youth and fam­i­lies.</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­mor­row, 11am</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: Free with regis­tra­tion INFO: www.face­book.com/ Gate­wayTheatre­SG</p>


